Welcome to GM3ZZA CW Trainer - ZZACWT.

Installation Instructions - Linux:

1. Ensure you have the necessary dependencies installed.

Make sure that you have cmake and the gnu tools.
   
FLTK can either be compiled from source cloned from github 
(https://github.com/fltk/fltk) or installed form a tarball. 
It is also available in most distros. Version 1.4.3 
or greater is required.

Nlohmann/json can either be compiled from source cloned from 
github (https://github.com/nlohmann/json).
It is also available in most distros.

Install the following packages on Debian/Ubuntu:
   sudo apt install cmake build-essential \
   doxygen texlive-latex-base texlive-latex-extra 


1. Clone the latest version of the code from the GitHub repository:
   git clone https://github.com/pvrose/zzalog.git

2. Navigate to the project directory and run the following commands
to build ZZACWT.
   cd zzalog
   cmake -B build -DZZACWT_DOX=ON
   cmake --build build -j4

3. After the build process is complete, you can find the 
executable in the build directory: build/zzacwt.

4. To install. This may need to be run as supervisor.
   cmake --install build

5. Alternatively to build and install as user, you can use the following command:
   cmake --install build --prefix ~/.local


